cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper proposes a method for video-based person re-identification, which involves extracting spatial and temporal features from videos. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new type of convolution network, which involves multi-scale 3D convolution layers, indicating that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper involves attention mechanisms, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, which could also place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
